<h1>Who...</h1>
	<p>
	Marist College and  IBM Joint Studies are joining in on research and development of the OpenFlow
	protocol in hopes of progressing the adaptivity of the protocol in modern 
	networks.
	<h4>Partners</h4>
		<ul>
		   <li>IBM</li>
		</ul>
	</p>
<h1>What...</h1>
	<p>
	Marist and IBM are in the development phase of an OpenFlow research and testing
	lab at Marist College in New York. The lab will allow for testing, research and 
	development of the OpenFlow protocol. Specific documentation on what we are doing will be available soon.
	</p>
<h1>Our Goal...</h1>
	<p>
	The goal of the research OpenFlow facility in Marist College's Enterprise
	 Computing Research Lab is to allow for:
		<ul>
			<li>Development of Openflow capable SDN applications</li>
			<li>Research in the areas of scalability and reliablity</li>
			<li>Testing and Research of Openflow Switches and Devices</li>
			<li>Allow students to work with a leading edge technology</li>
		</ul>
	</p>
